Requisition Title -
Data Analyst - Product Forensics
Job Number: - AUS120933
Description

Job Title: Data Analyst – Product Forensics
Location: Melbourne
Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head
Get stuck into our huge data sets to create solutions for our customers
Join a progressive organisation with the people and policies you want
At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive and to achieve this, we need a talented Data Analyst to join our Product Forensic squad. The purpose of the Product Forensics Analytics Squad is to ensure we do the right thing by our customers, to build and sustain trust. We work to fulfil our mission through the ongoing prevention and detection of “the unexpected” so that the customer experience is seamless and reliable.
As a Senior Product Forensics Consultant focused on the newly formed Product Forensics operation/domain, you will bring extensive analytical and technical skills, business acumen and natural curiosity to support and enable your squad to deliver on a wide range of analytical investigations and initiatives to provide valued insights and enable data-driven decision making.
Additionally, you will be tried and tested methods that can be shared across the team, lead forensics engagements and investigations and mentor up and coming data analysts.

What a typical day might look like
Support individual missions of Squads through data analysis
Attend stand-up to align progress on your individual tasks
Perform product and forensics analytics to detect and prevent “the unexpected” across the Retail and Commercial Bank product sets to drive continuous improvement and positively influence strategic change
Perform deep drives into high-risk areas to determine root causes and improvement opportunities with Technology and Product areas.
Build continuous monitoring mechanisms to proactively manage, prevent and detect product risks across Australia Division and drive immediate action
Upskill product areas in data analytics to enable them to become self-sufficient

What will likely be in your toolkit?
Experiences in driving in-depth investigations or analytical engagements to uncover root causes, behaviours, trends and anomalies for decision making purposes.
Experiences in designing/building continuous monitoring and diagnostics mechanisms to scale.
Skills to quickly understand, interrogate and investigate large datasets utilising a variety of methods (SQL, Python, R) and technologies (Teradata, Hadoop, SAS, Cloudera, Excel)
Ability to break down problems and plan out manageable work activities through Human Centred Design, Hypothesis Based Thinking or Structured Problem Solving approaches.
Ability to mentor, review and challenge team members’ investigations to assure quality and outcome delivery.
Ability to communicate and present ideas and outcomes to technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Ability to manage multiple investigations at once and adapt to changing priorities and ambiguity.
You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture and we actively encourage people to try new things. So if this role interests you and you feel you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

About ANZ
We’re reinventing the way we do banking, and our community of collaborative, innovative thinkers who create human centred solutions are helping us get there. We’re responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter and helping people achieve incredible things – be it buying their home, building a business or saving for things big or small.
We support our people by providing a range of flexible working options so they can work in the way that best suits them. We encourage you to talk to us about your need for flexibility and any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself.
We’ll also offer you the opportunity to develop your career, working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated and create a great place to grow, thrive and belong.
Interested in joining us? Click Apply now, or visit www.anz.com/careers to find out more or view other opportunities.

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest


Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1
Salary range: $74,406.00 - $100,090.00
Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

Key skills required
1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.
Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Weekend work required


Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

Our Commitment to Diversity
NSW Health values diversity and is committed to building an inclusive workplace culture that reflects the community we serve. We encourage applications from diverse community groups including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, LGBTIQ+, those with special needs and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

For any technical issues, contact Recruitment at HSSG-Recruitment@health.nsw.gov.au.

Please note that not everyone who expresses their interest will be called to work in the centres.

About Swanky

We are a fast-growing Digital Consulting and eCommerce agency. We are leaders in the Shopify movement in Europe and are quickly making inroads into the US, Canadian and Australian markets.

Our focus is on creating nimble, flexible and cost-effective enterprise ecommerce solutions using Shopify Plus - the fastest growing Enterprise eCommerce platform on the planet.

Within the Growth Accelerator team, we have specialists that make up a full-service ecommerce function: CRO strategists, Performance Marketeers, UX Designers, SEO & Content Specialists & Project Managers.

We are looking for a Data Analyst with experience in CRO and customer insight development to help us cement our position as the best agency in the sector

Responsibility / Skills

Develop our analytical process - particularly expediting how we turn customer data into insight and therefore action
Developing flexible insight solutions across every stage of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion and retention) to facilitate quicker learnings.
Coaching and mentoring to up skill the company through advancing their use of data, including analysis, interpretation and presentation of data
Turn data and ideas into action by supporting the team with test ideation, strategy and presentation (including supporting with every stage of the testing process)
Internal reporting - this role could handle internal reporting (on our impact), and client reporting (both internally for learning and for the client) with a view to establishing ourselves as the source of truth for our clients data-led decisions
Research and development - advising and assisting with the analytical setup and ongoing management of new websites. To include the research and development of analytical opportunities during and prior to the new build stage of client engagement

This will involve having skills in the following areas:

Data analysis across all stages of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion & retention) and all areas of ecommerce performance.
Being able to create a story that communicates customer behaviour and reporting on client performance.
Being data curious and have the capability to out what the data says, and more importantly, why
Be a great data communicator - being able to relay data in a way that is accessible to everyone
Enjoy collaborating on projects

Be a problem solver and enjoy being able to find the solution to a business/customer issue

(Ideally) proven experience in a data analytics and conversion rate optimisation role
(Ideally) experience using split testing software
Familiarity with Agile frameworks
Ability to document and troubleshoot errors
Excellent communication skills
Attention to detail
Analytical mind and problem-solving aptitude
Strong organisational skills
Familiarity with web technologies such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript useful but not a pre-requisite

Benefits:

Starting salary of $60k-$75k
Opportunity to grow and shape the position
Personal development within a fast-growing company
Opportunities to travel to work with remote working teams
Collaborative, creative working environment
Regular company socials and events, including Games Nights, and lunchtime sports

The successful candidate will have experience of working in health research data, have a high attention to detail, a proactive approach and strong time management skills.

Job Title: Start your new career as a Data Analyst
Job Description:
Data is exploding
The demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.
The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of great data analysts and data scientists.
If you are passionate about data,we have the best way to get you into your new data career.
How does it work?
The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx.
In addition, you will be trained in all the soft skills needed to become a consultant from our team of experts.
The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.
Do I get paid to learn?
Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.
Key dates
The Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round is February, June and October.
The applications for the February 2021 intake close on the 7th December, 2020.
What’s in it for you
Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technology
Become a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platform
It’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultant
Gain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in Australia
Learn from the best data and analytics experts in Australia
Study in a creative work space in central Sydney
Details of the role
Four months of classroom training
Four client engagements, each 6 months long
The result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant
$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second year
We’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in Australia
When you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to you
What we’re looking for
Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience.
What we are looking for is :
Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every day
Data-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomes
Tech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy it
Curiosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and why
Resourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re asking
Fast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this role
Creativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible forms
Application Process
We do things differently and we’re proud of it.
So forget about the application process you might be used to.
Here’s how the process works:
Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.
Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.
Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.
Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!
Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us by filling in the application form on our website! https://www.thedataschool.com.au/apply/
The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the application
We are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

ADF Transition is seeking a high performing APS 6 to join the Business Intelligence (BI) team in the role of Data Analyst. Multiple years’ experience in in data extraction, cleaning, testing and data.

About the team

The Safety, Environment and Regulation division upholds safety and sustainability in our transport system. We’re working to deliver globally-recognised, safe, sustainable transport for our people, customers and the community.

The opportunity

Right now, we have an opportunity for a Senior Data Analyst to join us in our Research & Evaluation team.

This is a Temporary full time opportunity, up to October 2021. This position will be looking to move to Macquarie Park in the near future however with the current COVID environment the incumbent of the role will be working from home.

You will be responsible for providing data and analysis to support monitoring and evaluation of road safety initiatives. You will be required to extract, analyse, interpret, manage and provide accurate information regarding crash and other relevant road safety data and evidence using Crashlink and Geographic Information Systems including ArcGIS and other relevant spatial packages.

You will be involved in:
Define data needs based on research and evaluation scope and advice of key Centre for Road Safety staff, and sort and clean datasets to meet defined data needs (e.g. analysis of Road User Movement codes and spatial buffering of relevant data).
Extract and process crash and other road safety data to meet those defined needs and assist staff in accessing and using various data and information sources. This includes building new datasets and running queries.
Converting crash and GIS data into useful information for the purpose of ongoing program improvement and evaluating program effectiveness, including assessing whether intended safety benefits of the program were realised.

This role reports to the Principal Research Scientist.

Essential Requirements:
Relevant tertiary qualification or equivalent experience.
Demonstrated experience in the use of ArcGIS
Experience analysing road infrastructure data (traffic signals, sealed shoulders, safety barriers etc.)

Salary and Benefits

Job Title: Data Analyst – Product Forensics

Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head

Join a progressive organisation with the people and policies you want
At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive and to achieve this, we need a talented Data Analyst to join our Product Forensic squad. The purpose of the Product Forensics Analytics Squad is to ensure we do the right thing by our customers, to build and sustain trust. We work to fulfil our mission through the ongoing prevention and detection of “the unexpected” so that the customer experience is seamless and reliable.
As a Senior Product Forensics Consultant focused on the newly formed Product Forensics operation/domain, you will bring extensive analytical and technical skills, business acumen and natural curiosity to support and enable your squad to deliver on a wide range of analytical investigations and initiatives to provide valued insights and enable data-driven decision making.
Additionally, you will be tried and tested methods that can be shared across the team, lead forensics engagements and investigations and mentor up and coming data analysts.

What a typical day might look like
Support individual missions of Squads through data analysis
Attend stand-up to align progress on your individual tasks
Perform product and forensics analytics to detect and prevent “the unexpected” across the Retail and Commercial Bank product sets to drive continuous improvement and positively influence strategic change
Perform deep drives into high-risk areas to determine root causes and improvement opportunities with Technology and Product areas.
Build continuous monitoring mechanisms to proactively manage, prevent and detect product risks across Australia Division and drive immediate action
Upskill product areas in data analytics to enable them to become self-sufficient

What will likely be in your toolkit?
Experiences in driving in-depth investigations or analytical engagements to uncover root causes, behaviours, trends and anomalies for decision making purposes.
Experiences in designing/building continuous monitoring and diagnostics mechanisms to scale.
Skills to quickly understand, interrogate and investigate large datasets utilising a variety of methods (SQL, Python, R) and technologies (Teradata, Hadoop, SAS, Cloudera, Excel)
Ability to break down problems and plan out manageable work activities through Human Centred Design, Hypothesis Based Thinking or Structured Problem Solving approaches.
Ability to mentor, review and challenge team members’ investigations to assure quality and outcome delivery.
Ability to communicate and present ideas and outcomes to technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Ability to manage multiple investigations at once and adapt to changing priorities and ambiguity.
You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture and we actively encourage people to try new things. So if this role interests you and you feel you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

We’re reinventing the way we do banking, and our community of collaborative, innovative thinkers who create human centred solutions are helping us get there. We’re responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter and helping people achieve incredible things – be it buying their home, building a business or saving for things big or small.

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest


Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1
Salary range: $74,406.00 - $100,090.00
Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

Key skills required
1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.
Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Weekend work required


Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

NSW Health values diversity and is committed to building an inclusive workplace culture that reflects the community we serve. We encourage applications from diverse community groups including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, LGBTIQ+, those with special needs and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

Job Title: Start your new career as a Data Analyst
Job Description:
Data is exploding
The demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.
The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of great data analysts and data scientists.
If you are passionate about data,we have the best way to get you into your new data career.
How does it work?
The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx.
In addition, you will be trained in all the soft skills needed to become a consultant from our team of experts.
The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.
Do I get paid to learn?
Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.
Key dates
The Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round is February, June and October.
The applications for the February 2021 intake close on the 7th December, 2020.
What’s in it for you
Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technology
Become a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platform
It’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultant
Gain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in Australia
Learn from the best data and analytics experts in Australia
Study in a creative work space in central Sydney
Details of the role
Four months of classroom training
Four client engagements, each 6 months long
The result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant
$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second year
We’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in Australia
When you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to you
What we’re looking for
Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience.
What we are looking for is :
Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every day
Data-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomes
Tech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy it
Curiosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and why
Resourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re asking
Fast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this role
Creativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible forms
Application Process
We do things differently and we’re proud of it.
So forget about the application process you might be used to.
Here’s how the process works:
Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.
Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.
Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.
Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!
Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us by filling in the application form on our website! https://www.thedataschool.com.au/apply/
The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the application
We are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

Description

Job Title: Data Analyst – Product Forensics
Location: Melbourne
Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head
Get stuck into our huge data sets to create solutions for our customers
Join a progressive organisation with the people and policies you want
At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive and to achieve this, we need a talented Data Analyst to join our Product Forensic squad. The purpose of the Product Forensics Analytics Squad is to ensure we do the right thing by our customers, to build and sustain trust. We work to fulfil our mission through the ongoing prevention and detection of “the unexpected” so that the customer experience is seamless and reliable.
As a Senior Product Forensics Consultant focused on the newly formed Product Forensics operation/domain, you will bring extensive analytical and technical skills, business acumen and natural curiosity to support and enable your squad to deliver on a wide range of analytical investigations and initiatives to provide valued insights and enable data-driven decision making.
Additionally, you will be tried and tested methods that can be shared across the team, lead forensics engagements and investigations and mentor up and coming data analysts.

What a typical day might look like
Support individual missions of Squads through data analysis
Attend stand-up to align progress on your individual tasks
Perform product and forensics analytics to detect and prevent “the unexpected” across the Retail and Commercial Bank product sets to drive continuous improvement and positively influence strategic change
Perform deep drives into high-risk areas to determine root causes and improvement opportunities with Technology and Product areas.
Build continuous monitoring mechanisms to proactively manage, prevent and detect product risks across Australia Division and drive immediate action
Upskill product areas in data analytics to enable them to become self-sufficient

What will likely be in your toolkit?
Experiences in driving in-depth investigations or analytical engagements to uncover root causes, behaviours, trends and anomalies for decision making purposes.
Experiences in designing/building continuous monitoring and diagnostics mechanisms to scale.
Skills to quickly understand, interrogate and investigate large datasets utilising a variety of methods (SQL, Python, R) and technologies (Teradata, Hadoop, SAS, Cloudera, Excel)
Ability to break down problems and plan out manageable work activities through Human Centred Design, Hypothesis Based Thinking or Structured Problem Solving approaches.
Ability to mentor, review and challenge team members’ investigations to assure quality and outcome delivery.
Ability to communicate and present ideas and outcomes to technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Ability to manage multiple investigations at once and adapt to changing priorities and ambiguity.
You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture and we actively encourage people to try new things. So if this role interests you and you feel you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

About ANZ
We’re reinventing the way we do banking, and our community of collaborative, innovative thinkers who create human centred solutions are helping us get there. We’re responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter and helping people achieve incredible things – be it buying their home, building a business or saving for things big or small.

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest


Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1
Salary range: $74,406.00 - $100,090.00
Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

Key skills required
1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.
Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Weekend work required


Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

In this role you will be working alongside our research, statistical and database teams.
This is a fantastic opportunity to gain experience within an internationally recognised research organisation involved in the analysis and dissemination of data from large-scale observational studies and pragmatic randomised controlled trials.
The successful candidate will have experience of working in health research data, have a high attention to detail, a proactive approach and strong time management skills.

· Advise internal team members and external clients on study database(s) content

· Undertake quality checks to assure high standards of data and code
· Contribute to data analyses as required for research projects

· Experience in at least one of the following statistical packages: R (preferred), Python (data science toolkits, particularly Pandas, ggplot, Scikit Learn, Tensorflow, Keras), or Stata
· Experience working with relational databases (such as SQL Server), clinical or medical research, working with big data
· Statistical background (models, correlations, hypothesis), and database administration tools (migration, DB administration)
· Experience of working with real-life clinical databases /EMRs /registry data
· Strong in data analysis, interpretation, and visualization
Preferred Experience:
· Natural Language Processing and use of regular expressions in R or Python, particularly in text-mining software (e.g. Python's spaCy)
· Automating generation of regular reports, through R Markdown, Jupyter notebooks, or another report-generation software

Job Title: Start your new career as a Data Analyst
Job Description:
Data is exploding
The demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.
The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of great data analysts and data scientists.
If you are passionate about data,we have the best way to get you into your new data career.
How does it work?
The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx.
In addition, you will be trained in all the soft skills needed to become a consultant from our team of experts.
The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.
Do I get paid to learn?
Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.
Key dates
The Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round is February, June and October.
The applications for the February 2021 intake close on the 7th December, 2020.
What’s in it for you
Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technology
Become a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platform
It’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultant
Gain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in Australia
Learn from the best data and analytics experts in Australia
Study in a creative work space in central Sydney
Details of the role
Four months of classroom training
Four client engagements, each 6 months long

Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.

5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.

Weekend work required

Job Description: Data Analyst

About Swanky

We are a fast-growing Digital Consulting and eCommerce agency. We are leaders in the Shopify movement in Europe and are quickly making inroads into the US, Canadian and Australian markets.

Our focus is on creating nimble, flexible and cost-effective enterprise ecommerce solutions using Shopify Plus - the fastest growing Enterprise eCommerce platform on the planet.

Our growth has been achieved by helping our clients maximise their commercial potential through our Growth Accelerator service. Within the Growth Accelerator team, we have specialists that make up a full-service ecommerce function: CRO strategists, Performance Marketeers, UX Designers, SEO & Content Specialists & Project Managers.

We are looking for a Data Analyst with experience in CRO and customer insight development to help us cement our position as the best agency in the sector

Responsibility / Skills

Develop our analytical process - particularly expediting how we turn customer data into insight and therefore action
Developing flexible insight solutions across every stage of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion and retention) to facilitate quicker learnings.
Coaching and mentoring to up skill the company through advancing their use of data, including analysis, interpretation and presentation of data
Turn data and ideas into action by supporting the team with test ideation, strategy and presentation (including supporting with every stage of the testing process)
Internal reporting - this role could handle internal reporting (on our impact), and client reporting (both internally for learning and for the client) with a view to establishing ourselves as the source of truth for our clients data-led decisions
Research and development - advising and assisting with the analytical setup and ongoing management of new websites. To include the research and development of analytical opportunities during and prior to the new build stage of client engagement

This will involve having skills in the following areas:

Data analysis across all stages of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion & retention) and all areas of ecommerce performance.
Being able to create a story that communicates customer behaviour and reporting on client performance.
Being data curious and have the capability to out what the data says, and more importantly, why
Be a great data communicator - being able to relay data in a way that is accessible to everyone
Enjoy collaborating on projects
Be able to create an insight generation programme, including knowing how to understand the customer, process and interpret the data
Be a problem solver and enjoy being able to find the solution to a business/customer issue

Requirements

(Ideally) proven experience in a data analytics and conversion rate optimisation role
(Ideally) experience using split testing software
Familiarity with Agile frameworks
Ability to document and troubleshoot errors
Excellent communication skills
Attention to detail
Analytical mind and problem-solving aptitude
Strong organisational skills
Familiarity with web technologies such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript useful but not a pre-requisite

Benefits:

Starting salary of $60k-$75k
Opportunity to grow and shape the position
Personal development within a fast-growing company
Opportunities to travel to work with remote working teams
Collaborative, creative working environment
Regular company socials and events, including Games Nights, and lunchtime sports

About us:
We’re known for being the country’s most popular rewards program, making the everyday worth more for millions of Aussies. But 26 years of success and growth doesn’t happen by keeping up the status quo.
All the things that make working at Flybuys different as usual – these aren't just values we talk about. They’re built into everything we do, every day.

And together we can make every day different as usual.
Your Team:
We've already built a pretty amazing team, but we're not looking for more of the same. Our day-to-day is made stronger when we surround ourselves with people who are different, like you.
We work really hard to build teams that support each other. It’s the kind of environment you’ll miss while you’re on holidays.

There is no typical working week at Flybuys. But here are some of the things you might be working on, day-to-day;
Work with Analytics and Commercial teams to articulate the customer opportunity, commercial benefit, analytical findings.

Source, develop and apply new and existing analytical methods and techniques.
Use of a variety of sources to keep abreast of industry practices.

Naturally collaborative with a strong emphasis on building and leveraging relationships both internally and externally.
Experience of large, complex data sets.
Naturally curious, able to positively challenge existing practices.
Experience of analytical tools – data extraction, data exploration and analysis, data visualisation.
Experience of working within large, complex, cross functional projects .
Technical skills including Oracle SQL, R, BI experience (e.g.Tableau, MicroStrategy)
Experience with Snowflake would be advantageous.
We value ways of working that work for everyone, and use our different strengths to make us stronger.
We work hard to make sure everyone’s voice is heard and respected equally, regardless of identity, background, position, ability or lifestyle.
So whether you’re an earlybird list maker, a night owl coder, a brainstorm chaser or a PowerPoint proof-reader, we want you to Be You, With Us.

Does supporting world-class research and improving lives of patients excite you? Our dynamic and internationally recognised research company Optimum Patient Care, (OPC) is looking for a highly motivated and dynamic member to join our data team. The role can be based in one of our Singapore, Cambridge, or Brisbane offices. For experienced individuals, remote working may also be considered. In this role you will be working alongside our research, statistical and database teams.
This is a fantastic opportunity to gain experience within an internationally recognised research organisation involved in the analysis and dissemination of data from large-scale observational studies and pragmatic randomised controlled trials.
The successful candidate will have experience of working in health research data, have a high attention to detail, a proactive approach and strong time management skills.
Primary responsibilities:
· Provide support on database querying, population, and reporting, using structured query language (SQL)
· Statistical analysis using R
· Generate data releases following study protocol requirements and service reports (Jupyter notebooks, RMarkdown)
· Improve the interpretation of medical free text with Natural Language Processing skills
· Advise internal team members and external clients on study database(s) content
· Engage in building and maintaining data dictionaries and system technical documentation
· Undertake quality checks to assure high standards of data and code
· Contribute to data analyses as required for research projects
· Maintain compliance with information governance and company policies
Qualifications Required:
MSc preferred, with strong technical or scientific component (e.g. Computer Science, Math, Statistics). BSc or equivalent will be considered for candidates with additional relevant experience.
Essential Experience:
· Expertise in Structured Query Language (SQL) and database processing (ETL, stored procedures, large datasets)
· Experience in at least one of the following statistical packages: R (preferred), Python (data science toolkits, particularly Pandas, ggplot, Scikit Learn, Tensorflow, Keras), or Stata
· Experience working with relational databases (such as SQL Server), clinical or medical research, working with big data
· Statistical background (models, correlations, hypothesis), and database administration tools (migration, DB administration)
· Experience of working with real-life clinical databases /EMRs /registry data
· Strong in data analysis, interpretation, and visualization
Preferred Experience:
· Natural Language Processing and use of regular expressions in R or Python, particularly in text-mining software (e.g. Python's spaCy)
· Automating generation of regular reports, through R Markdown, Jupyter notebooks, or another report-generation software
· Data dictionaries and advanced documentation systems
Contract and Salary
Part-time and full-time roles are considered.
Starting salary is dependent on qualifications and your experience.
Immediate start is available.

Permitted to work permanently with no restriction on hours (e.g. citizen, permanent resident) (Preferred)

Job Title: Start your new career as a Data Analyst
Job Description:
Data is exploding
The demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.
The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of great data analysts and data scientists.
If you are passionate about data,we have the best way to get you into your new data career.
How does it work?
The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx.
In addition, you will be trained in all the soft skills needed to become a consultant from our team of experts.
The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.
Do I get paid to learn?
Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.
Key dates
The Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round is February, June and October.
The applications for the February 2021 intake close on the 7th December, 2020.
What’s in it for you
Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technology
Become a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platform
It’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultant
Gain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in Australia
Learn from the best data and analytics experts in Australia
Study in a creative work space in central Sydney
Details of the role
Four months of classroom training
Four client engagements, each 6 months long
The result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant
$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second year
We’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in Australia
When you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to you
What we’re looking for
Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience.
What we are looking for is :
Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every day
Data-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomes
Tech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy it
Curiosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and why
Resourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re asking
Fast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this role
Creativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible forms
Application Process
We do things differently and we’re proud of it.
So forget about the application process you might be used to.
Here’s how the process works:
Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.
Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.
Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.
Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!
Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us by filling in the application form on our website! https://www.thedataschool.com.au/apply/
The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the application
We are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

Salary: $50,000.00 – $60,000.00 per year

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest


Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1
Salary range: $74,406.00 - $100,090.00
Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

Key skills required
1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.
Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Weekend work required


Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

Our Commitment to Diversity
NSW Health values diversity and is committed to building an inclusive workplace culture that reflects the community we serve. We encourage applications from diverse community groups including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, LGBTIQ+, those with special needs and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

For any technical issues, contact Recruitment at HSSG-Recruitment@health.nsw.gov.au.

Please note that not everyone who expresses their interest will be called to work in the centres.

Job Description: Data Analyst

About Swanky

We are a fast-growing Digital Consulting and eCommerce agency. We are leaders in the Shopify movement in Europe and are quickly making inroads into the US, Canadian and Australian markets.

Our focus is on creating nimble, flexible and cost-effective enterprise ecommerce solutions using Shopify Plus - the fastest growing Enterprise eCommerce platform on the planet.

Our growth has been achieved by helping our clients maximise their commercial potential through our Growth Accelerator service. Within the Growth Accelerator team, we have specialists that make up a full-service ecommerce function: CRO strategists, Performance Marketeers, UX Designers, SEO & Content Specialists & Project Managers.

We are looking for a Data Analyst with experience in CRO and customer insight development to help us cement our position as the best agency in the sector

Responsibility / Skills

Develop our analytical process - particularly expediting how we turn customer data into insight and therefore action
Developing flexible insight solutions across every stage of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion and retention) to facilitate quicker learnings.
Coaching and mentoring to up skill the company through advancing their use of data, including analysis, interpretation and presentation of data
Turn data and ideas into action by supporting the team with test ideation, strategy and presentation (including supporting with every stage of the testing process)
Internal reporting - this role could handle internal reporting (on our impact), and client reporting (both internally for learning and for the client) with a view to establishing ourselves as the source of truth for our clients data-led decisions
Research and development - advising and assisting with the analytical setup and ongoing management of new websites. To include the research and development of analytical opportunities during and prior to the new build stage of client engagement

This will involve having skills in the following areas:

Data analysis across all stages of the customer journey (acquisition, conversion & retention) and all areas of ecommerce performance.
Being able to create a story that communicates customer behaviour and reporting on client performance.
Being data curious and have the capability to out what the data says, and more importantly, why
Be a great data communicator - being able to relay data in a way that is accessible to everyone
Enjoy collaborating on projects
Be able to create an insight generation programme, including knowing how to understand the customer, process and interpret the data
Be a problem solver and enjoy being able to find the solution to a business/customer issue

Requirements

(Ideally) proven experience in a data analytics and conversion rate optimisation role
(Ideally) experience using split testing software
Familiarity with Agile frameworks
Ability to document and troubleshoot errors
Excellent communication skills
Attention to detail
Analytical mind and problem-solving aptitude
Strong organisational skills
Familiarity with web technologies such as HTML, CSS, JavaScript useful but not a pre-requisite

Benefits:

Starting salary of $60k-$75k
Opportunity to grow and shape the position
Personal development within a fast-growing company
Opportunities to travel to work with remote working teams
Collaborative, creative working environment
Regular company socials and events, including Games Nights, and lunchtime sports

About us:
We’re known for being the country’s most popular rewards program, making the everyday worth more for millions of Aussies. But 26 years of success and growth doesn’t happen by keeping up the status quo.

· Contribute to data analyses as required for research projects

· Experience in at least one of the following statistical packages: R (preferred), Python (data science toolkits, particularly Pandas, ggplot, Scikit Learn, Tensorflow, Keras), or Stata
· Experience working with relational databases (such as SQL Server), clinical or medical research, working with big data
· Statistical background (models, correlations, hypothesis), and database administration tools (migration, DB administration)
· Experience of working with real-life clinical databases /EMRs /registry data
· Strong in data analysis, interpretation, and visualization
Preferred Experience:
· Natural Language Processing and use of regular expressions in R or Python, particularly in text-mining software (e.g. Python's spaCy)

Job Title: Start your new career as a Data Analyst
Job Description:
Data is exploding
The demand for great data analysts and data scientists has never been higher than it is today. There simply aren't enough to fill the positions being advertised.
The Data School Australia is creating the next generation of great data analysts and data scientists.
If you are passionate about data,we have the best way to get you into your new data career.
How does it work?
The successful applicants will be immersed into 4 months of intensive classroom training based on the market-leading technologies, Tableau and Alteryx.
In addition, you will be trained in all the soft skills needed to become a consultant from our team of experts.
The classroom training is followed by four 6-month client engagements with Australia's leading organisations to give you real-world experience to kick-start your new career.
Do I get paid to learn?
Yes. The Data School offers you a competitive salary while you study and gain valuable industry experience.
Key dates
The Data School takes new consultants three times each year. The starting dates for each round is February, June and October.
The applications for the February 2021 intake close on the 7th December, 2020.
What’s in it for you
Become a guru in Tableau, the market-leading data visualisation technology
Become a guru in Alteryx, the market-leading data analytics platform
It’s not just data that’s important – learn soft skills that are crucial for your success as a data consultant
Gain real-world experience by working with the leading organisations in Australia
Learn from the best data and analytics experts in Australia
Study in a creative work space in central Sydney
Details of the role
Four months of classroom training
Four client engagements, each 6 months long
The result is a 28 month, fixed-term contract to start your new career as a data consultant
$56,000 per annum that will increase in the second year
We’re sorry – we can’t sponsor you, so make sure you can work in Australia
When you finish the contract, the world is your oyster. You can stay on as a consultant and work on some fascinating projects or step out into the big wide world of data that has been opened up to you
What we’re looking for
Here at the Data School, we don’t look at what’s on your CV or your experience.
What we are looking for is :
Passion – we want you to want it, to have a true desire to learn and motivation to improve yourself and your skills every day
Data-driven minds - you love the idea of immersing yourself in data to drive meaningful insights and create jaw-dropping outcomes
Tech-Savvy – we don’t need you to have experience, but working with tech comes naturally to you, and you enjoy it
Curiosity – questions are falling out of your mouth, you always want to know how and why
Resourcefulness – sometimes, the answers aren’t always in front of you, you’ll need ingenuity and resourcefulness to find answers to those questions you’re asking
Fast learner – picking new things up every day whilst retaining previous knowledge will help you be successful in this role
Creativity - the goal is delivering outcomes. You’ll need creativity to deliver those outcomes in meaningful, digestible forms
Application Process
We do things differently and we’re proud of it.
So forget about the application process you might be used to.
Here’s how the process works:
Join Tableau - Join the community and download Tableau Public by creating a new account.
Get inspired – Check out Tableau Public Gallery, there are brilliant examples for you to look at and research.
Find your data - Choose any data set you want! We mean it; from politics to sport, TV and popular culture. Tableau provide many data sets on their resources page.
Create your Viz - Now the fun begins! Once you have your data set, you can begin creating your winning viz!
Share it with us - Once your work is live on Tableau Public, send it to us by filling in the application form on our website! https://www.thedataschool.com.au/apply/
The Interview - If you impress us with your passion, innovation and understanding of data, you will be invited to an interview with our Head Coach and you've started the application
We are taking applications at all times. If you share the same inquisitive nature, have a passion for getting to the truth by way of data, then we’d love to hear from you!

Requisition Title -
Data Analyst - Product Forensics
Job Number: - AUS120933
Description

Job Title: Data Analyst – Product Forensics
Location: Melbourne
Help shape the future as we leverage data to flip traditional banking on its head
Get stuck into our huge data sets to create solutions for our customers
Join a progressive organisation with the people and policies you want
At ANZ our purpose is to shape a world where people and communities thrive and to achieve this, we need a talented Data Analyst to join our Product Forensic squad. The purpose of the Product Forensics Analytics Squad is to ensure we do the right thing by our customers, to build and sustain trust. We work to fulfil our mission through the ongoing prevention and detection of “the unexpected” so that the customer experience is seamless and reliable.
As a Senior Product Forensics Consultant focused on the newly formed Product Forensics operation/domain, you will bring extensive analytical and technical skills, business acumen and natural curiosity to support and enable your squad to deliver on a wide range of analytical investigations and initiatives to provide valued insights and enable data-driven decision making.
Additionally, you will be tried and tested methods that can be shared across the team, lead forensics engagements and investigations and mentor up and coming data analysts.

What a typical day might look like
Support individual missions of Squads through data analysis
Attend stand-up to align progress on your individual tasks
Perform product and forensics analytics to detect and prevent “the unexpected” across the Retail and Commercial Bank product sets to drive continuous improvement and positively influence strategic change
Perform deep drives into high-risk areas to determine root causes and improvement opportunities with Technology and Product areas.
Build continuous monitoring mechanisms to proactively manage, prevent and detect product risks across Australia Division and drive immediate action
Upskill product areas in data analytics to enable them to become self-sufficient

What will likely be in your toolkit?
Experiences in driving in-depth investigations or analytical engagements to uncover root causes, behaviours, trends and anomalies for decision making purposes.
Experiences in designing/building continuous monitoring and diagnostics mechanisms to scale.
Skills to quickly understand, interrogate and investigate large datasets utilising a variety of methods (SQL, Python, R) and technologies (Teradata, Hadoop, SAS, Cloudera, Excel)
Ability to break down problems and plan out manageable work activities through Human Centred Design, Hypothesis Based Thinking or Structured Problem Solving approaches.
Ability to mentor, review and challenge team members’ investigations to assure quality and outcome delivery.
Ability to communicate and present ideas and outcomes to technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Ability to manage multiple investigations at once and adapt to changing priorities and ambiguity.
You’re not expected to have 100% of these skills. At ANZ a growth mindset is at the heart of our culture and we actively encourage people to try new things. So if this role interests you and you feel you have most of these things in your toolbox, we’d love to hear from you.

About ANZ
We’re reinventing the way we do banking, and our community of collaborative, innovative thinkers who create human centred solutions are helping us get there. We’re responding faster to changing customer requirements, focusing on the things that matter and helping people achieve incredible things – be it buying their home, building a business or saving for things big or small.
We support our people by providing a range of flexible working options so they can work in the way that best suits them. We encourage you to talk to us about your need for flexibility and any adjustments you may require to our recruitment process or the role itself.
We’ll also offer you the opportunity to develop your career, working in a diverse and inclusive workplace where the different backgrounds, perspectives and life experiences of our people are celebrated and create a great place to grow, thrive and belong.
Interested in joining us? Click Apply now, or visit www.anz.com/careers to find out more or view other opportunities.

Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) Expression of Interest


Thank you for your interest in assisting the NSW Health with the COVID-19 response.

We have opportunities to assist the Epidemiology and Surveillance Team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) based at St Leonards.

Who is eligible to express their interest?
Everyone who is:
an Australian Citizen, or
a permanent resident of Australia, or
a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or
a citizen of another country with an appropriate visa that allows you to work in Australia
persons interested in helping NSW Health with the COVID-19 response can apply for this role

What will a COVID-19 Data Analyst be doing?
The COVID-19 Data Analyst is part of the Epidemiology and surveillance team within the Public Health Response Branch (PHRB) responding to the COVID-19 Pandemic.
The Data Analyst is responsible for cleaning and preparing data from various sources for import into surveillance systems. The Data Analyst is responsible for providing high quality reliable data for the reporting team and other government users. The Data Analyst is responsible for analysis and enhancement of reporting data to provide high level and detailed daily, weekly and longer-term reports and visualisations. The Data Analyst will also respond to queries and information requests and other duties as required.


Working time
The PHRB is scheduled across 7 days a week over two shifts (8.30 am - 4 pm and 2.30 - 10 pm).

Remuneration
Classification: Health Manager Level 1
Salary range: $74,406.00 - $100,090.00
Hourly rate: $37.53 - $50.48

Key skills required
1. Data analysis skills and experience.
2. Experience with SAS and other data analysis platforms such as R.
3. Health or public health experience preferred.
4. Demonstrated high-level problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
5. Demonstrated excellent communication skills.
6. Knowledge and understanding of NSW Health policies, working process and guidelines.
7. Previous experience in data management and statistical computing.

Key accountabilities of the role
Prepare daily data extracts for import into the surveillance system.
Provide support for users working with reporting extracts in other government areas.
Liaise with data providers & subject matter experts to ensure correct translation between source data and stored data.
Prepare data for state-wide reporting.
Develop and maintain data pipeline code and improve code quality.

Key challenges
Work under time pressure to tight deadlines
High attention to detail required
Weekend work required


Things to consider when expressing interest:
Your availability will need to be across 7 days per week, for 5 shifts (morning and afternoon)
Weekend and/or evening work will be required

What do I need to provide?
Attach your current resume / curriculum vitae (CV) (maximum 5 pages) ONLY to the application
Complete the pre-screening questions on the application form.
Provide your availability including time frame/duration you are available.
2 x referees will need to be supplied prior to an offer being made.

Are you currently a NSW Government employee?
Current NSW Health, NSW Ministry of Health and NSW Government staff, must have their manager’s approval prior to expressing interest.
This will be an off-payroll arrangement for current Public Sector Staff, your agency can invoice NSW Health for salary expenses.
The team works on a shift work arrangement, you will be required to amend your working conditions to accommodate shift working.

Who will view my EOI?
Manager and Team leaders, of PHRB teams may review your expression of interest.

Our Commitment to Diversity
NSW Health values diversity and is committed to building an inclusive workplace culture that reflects the community we serve. We encourage applications from diverse community groups including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, LGBTIQ+, those with special needs and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

For any technical issues, contact Recruitment at HSSG-Recruitment@health.nsw.gov.au.

Please note that not everyone who expresses their interest will be called to work in the centres.

About Swanky

We are a fast-growing Digital Consulting and eCommerce agency. We are leaders in the Shopify movement in Europe and are quickly making inroads into the US, Canadian and Australian markets.

Our focus is on creating nimble, flexible and cost-effective enterprise ecommerce solutions using Shopify Plus - the fastest growing Enterprise eCommerce platform on the planet.
